1)Difference between QA and QC
QA (Quality Assurance)
  *QA is a proactive ,proccess oriented approach that aim to prevent defects by improve developement processes.
  *Goal: Prevent defects
  *Focus: Processes and procedures
  *Activities: Process design, documentation, audits, training, standardization
  *Timeline : occurs throughout entier product life cycel ,before and during developement.
  *Responsibility : involves  the entire team 
QC(Quality Control)
  QC is reactive ,product oriented approch that  aim to prevent detect and correct defect.
  *Goal: Detect defects
  *Focus: Final product/output
  *Activities: Inspection, testing, sampling, validation
  *Time line : primarlky occurs at the end of developement cycle ,during the testing phase .
  *Responsibility : usually performed by a  quality control team and specific person.

2)Explain in detail about STLC
   Software Tesing Life Cycle(STLC);
1. Requirement Analysis

Testers study requirements to identify what needs testing.
Understand functional & non-functional requirements
Identify testable areas
Prepare RTM (Requirement Traceability Matrix)
2. Test Planning
Defines the strategy for testing.
Decide scope, objectives, resources
Choose tools & testing types
Estimate time & cost
Deliverable: Test Plan Document
3. Test Case Development
Creation of test scenarios and cases.
Write test cases & test scripts Prepare test data Review and finalize test cases
4. Test Environment Setup
Prepare the environment where testing happens.
Smoke testing to verify setup
5. Test Execution
Actual testing phase.
Run test cases
Log defects (bugs)
Retest & perform regression testing
6. Test Closure
Wrap-up and evaluation.
Check test coverage Prepare test summary report and identify


